<HEAD>Three Officers Shot In Chicago Area Over Weekend</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 4th graf with 2 grafs to UPDATE with man in custody; no
pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man apparently seeking revenge because his
brother was ejected from a suburban nightclub entered the
establishment Sunday and shot an employee and an off-duty policeman,
critically wounding both, authorities said.
   In an unrelated case, two Chicago policemen wearing bulletproof
vests were slightly wounded when they were shot Saturday night at a
South Side federal housing project by a man wielding a shotgun,
police said.
   In west suburban Stone Park, the critically injured police
officer, Frank Costa, 40, and a night club employee were shot at
point-blank range with what police believe was a .357-caliber pistol.
   Pat Gleason, 24, of suburban Maywood, later surrendered to police
on a warrant charging him with aggravated battery, and additional
charges were being prepared, said Robert Natale, Stone Park deputy
chief of police.
   Natale said Gleason was being held on $1 million bond.
   In the Chicago housing project shootings, a 28-year-old Chicago
man was arrested, police said.
