<HEAD>Buses Collide, 15 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus carrying guests from a wedding
party collided with another bus near Bangkok and 15 people were
killed, police reported today.
   They said 30 people were injured in the accident Sunday in
Nonthaburi province 6 miles north of Bangkok.
   Police Capt. Kiat Changyoo said one bus was returning about 40
people to Bangkok from a wedding in Suphan Buri province and the
other belonged to folk singer Sunaree Ratchasima and was taking
instruments and equipment from Bangkok to a northern province where
she was scheduled to give a concert.
