<FIRST>u a AM-People'sChoice 3rdLd-Writethru a0445 03-13 0462</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People's Choice, 3rd Ld-Writethru, a0445,0474</SECOND>
<BYLINE>URGENT</BYLINE>
<HEAD>Eds: New throughout to reflect Cosby's continued dominance of the
awards; ADDS ``L.A. Law'' win in drama category; EDITS and DELETES outdated
material throughout. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURBANK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Comedian Bill Cosby dominated the People's
Choice Awards for the fifth straight year Sunday, followed by the
hit TV sitcom ``Roseanne'' and the film ``Rain Man.''
   Cosby was voted favorite male televison performer, favorite
all-around male star and his NBC series won favorite comedy in the
15th annual edition of the entertainment popularity contest
conducted by a nationwide Gallup Organization poll.
   Cosby was not present at the awards ceremony at Walt Disney
Studios here but thanked the public in a videotaped message in the
two-hour CBS national telecast presented by hosts Michael Landon and
Michele Lee.
   ``The Cosby Show'' also won all-time favorite television show
honors, edging longer-running hits ``MASH'' and ``Star Trek.''
   ``Roseanne'' star Roseanne Barr was named favorite female
performer in a new television series, the show was voted favorite
new television comedy series and co-star John Goodman was voted
favorite male performer in a new television series.
   ``I'd like to accept this award on behalf of all the working moms
and housewives,'' said Miss Barr, whose ABC-TV situation comedy
portrays the life of a blue-collar mother.
   ABC's ``China Beach'' was voted favorite new television dramatic
series and NBC's ``L.A. Law'' was selected as favorite television
dramatic series.
   Kirk Cameron of ABC-TV's ``Growing Pains'' was named favorite
young television performer and ``Cosby'' co-star Phylicia Rashad
took honors as favorite female television performer.
   The World War II saga ``War and Remembrance'' won best miniseries
honors. ``War and Remembrance,'' globe-spanning story of a family
torn by World War II, was based on Herman Wouk's novel of the same
name.
   The ABC-TV miniseries' disappointing ratings had led to
predictions that the miniseries format might be doomed.
   ```War and Remembrance' was an enormous undertaking and one that
required an almost unbelievable commitment from everyone involved in
the production,'' said miniseries star Robert Mitchum, who accepted
the award from Charlton Heston.
   In the film divisions, Cher was named favorite all-around female
star, while Hoffman was voted favorite actor in a dramatic motion
picture and his ``Rain Man'' was named favorite dramatic motion
picture.
   ``Big'' and ``Twins'' tied for favorite comedy motion picture,
while Eddie Murphy and Bette Midler were chosen as favorite male and
female actors in comedy motion pictures.
   Meryl Streep was voted favorite actress in a dramatic motion
picture.
   ``Gone With The Wind'' captured all-time favorite motion picture
honors.
   In music, Michael Jackson's ``Smooth Criminal'' received favorite
music video honors.
   Country singer Randy Travis was voted favorite male musical
performer and last year's female winner, Whitney Houston, once again
received favorite female musical performer honors.
</TEXT>
