<FIRST>r i PM-Pakistan     03-13 0147</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Pakistan,0151</SECOND>
<HEAD>Young Boy Killed in Karachi</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gunmen opened fire in a neighborhood in
this southern port city today and killed a 12-year-old boy, bringing
to six the death toll in three days of violence, police said.
   There was no claim of responsibility for the boy's death. Police
said the shooting occurred in a lower middle-class district in
western Karachi shortly after 1 a.m. Two people were injured, they
said.
   Army troops in machine-gun mounted vehicles patrolled parts of
the city to enforce a curfew aimed at ending the violence.
   In the past three years, ethnic clashes have left as many as 700
people dead in this city of 9 million, Pakistan's largest. The
clashes have been between ethnic Moslem natives and those who
immigrated from India.
   The latest violence began Saturday at Karachi University and
involved students from rival political groups.
</TEXT>
