<FIRST>r i AM-Demjanjuk     03-13 0197</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Demjanjuk,0203</SECOND>
<HEAD>Holocaust Survivor Convicted of Attacking Demjanjuk Lawyer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Holocaust survivor was convicted Monday of
aggravated assault for hurling acid in the face of a lawyer
representing convicted Nazi war criminal John Demjanjuk.
   Yisrael Yehezkieli, 70, was convicted after he confessed that he
threw acid in the face of Yoram Sheftel, Demjanjuk's defense
attorney, in December, Israel radio said.
   The incident occurred during the funeral of another Demjanjuk
attorney, Dov Eitan, who committed suicide. A woman standing next to
Sheftel suffered minor injuries during the acid attack.
   Yehezkieli will be sentenced May 4, the radio said. The crime
carries a maximum sentence of 20 years in jail.
   Sheftel still suffers eye damage because of the attack. As a
result, the appeal in Demjanjuk's conviction and death penalty has
been postponed until November.
   Demjanjuk, a 68-year-old Ohio autoworker, was sentenced to death
last year for crimes against humanity and against the Jewish people.
   He was convicted of being the guard ``Ivan the Terrible'' who
operated the gas chambers at the Treblinka death camp in
German-occupied Poland in World War II. About 850,000 Jews were
killed in Treblinka, including most members of Yehezkieli's family.
</TEXT>
