<HEAD>Names in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 4th item of PM-Names, a0449, recasting to CORRECT that
Roussel and Landhage not married, to CORRECT Landhage sted Langhage</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thierry Roussel says he's not ashamed to admit he
was still in love with a former lover during his few years of
marriage to Christina Onassis.
   ``Christina was the fire; Gaby was the calm. I loved them both
passionately,'' Roussel said in an interview in this week's People
magazine.
   Roussel fathered two children with former Swedish model Gaby
Landhage while he was married to Onassis and fathering their only
child, Athina. He and Onassis divorced in 1986 after Landhage became
pregnant a second time.
   Despite his tangled relations with the two women, Roussel said
Onassis ``became Gaby's friend'' and that the two women ``wanted the
children to grow up together.''
   Roussel said he would raise Athina ``with all the love a father
can have for his daughter.''
   The 4-year-old stands to inherit most of her mother's estimated
$500 million fortune. She is living with Roussel, Landhage and their
two children in Switzerland.
