<FIRST>r a AM-People-Williams     03-13 0293</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Williams,0299</SECOND>
<HEAD>Esther Williams, Star of Swim Movies, Takes Plunge Into Swimwear
Fashions</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LARRY NEUMEISTER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Esther Williams, who made plenty of big
splashes in 26 movies, is hoping for one more _ with a swimsuit line
designed to make her a friend in the fitting room for women of all
shapes and sizes.
   Williams, whose MGM movies like the ``Million Dollar Mermaid,''
``Dangerous When Wet'' and ``Bathing Beauty'' were known for lavish
swimming and underwater ballet sequences, says she packed decades of
swimming experience into 124 suit designs.
   In a telephone interview from her Beverly Hills, Calif., home,
Miss Williams said her $30- to $60-suits are sturdier and more
practical than other models. The line of suits made its debut Monday
in Houston and would be shown later in New York and Florida, said
Miss Williams.
   Using fabrics that were not available in the 1940s and 1950s,
when her films made her a top box office attraction, Miss Williams,
65, said she created bathing suits that are ``practical and
glamorous'' like the ones she swam in.
   ``We did a lot of surveys,'' she said. ``We discovered a lot of
women have gotten so unhappy with these high cut bathing suits that
are practically stripper clothes that they would like a couple of
models with a skirt back again.''
   The new suits will not ride up the back of a woman's body or fall
down on top in water, said Miss Williams. Even the bikinis in her
collection will not slip on the body, she promises.
   ``I've tested them myself,'' Miss Williams said. But she admitted
that when she goes out to her backyard pool for a daily workout, she
swims in the nude.
</TEXT>
