   The crew consisted of 19 Filipinos and four Britons. Sasaki
identified the captain as Rickard James, 50, from England.
   The cause of the fire was undetermined, Sasaki said.
   The Maasgusar was bound for Yokohama from Texas when it caught
fire about 60 miles off Nojimazaki, south of Tokyo, the official
said.
   The coast guard sent eight rescue boats and five Self-Defense
Force planes to combat the blaze.''
