<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell in relatively quiet trading Friday as the Dow
Jones average of 30 industrials dropped 9.29 to 2,282.14.
   Goverment bond prices tumbled and interest rates surged.
   The dollar finished higher against most major currencies.
   Soybean futures prices finished lower after gyrating widely,
grain futures finished mixed, silver futures gained while gold
retreated, livestock and meat futures advanced and energy futures
were mixed.
